e a nice Damage Shield when soloing.<br><br>The ninth ring is not terribly hard, Im working on it now. Someone on your server can definately make mind melt/tainted avelanche ale for you if you run around and collect the the stuff. Once you have the 9th ring you gain an additional 9sta and 50 hps.<br><br>At level 57 when doing the first 8 rings I made decent amounts of xp while doing the quests / waiting on certain spawns right in EW.<br><br>BTW this has by far been the most fun questing experience I have had in EQ.  <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>59 Knight of Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 804<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 9:04:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=257.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2 bits of advice please</span><hr size=1> ah yes the Dain ring, I am on 8th ring step myself, Gloradain is perma camped on Mith Marr atm. I have spent about 2 weeks not grinding AA to camp her, and also not getting the 8th ring, so I am taking a break from that now.<br><br>I did forget to mention the HP/ Mana on the talisman, which is kind of funny because those were the deciding factor in why I started wearing it over the collar. However, it is still less HP &amp; AC (tho more mana of course) than my Collar of the Storms, and for everyday use, MR is the only resist I worry much about, and collar of the storms has 7MR. <p><font size="+1">	<a href="http://www.geocities.